



Sir
Roxbury Camp Octr 23d 1775



You will Excuse me when I Trouble your Excellency so Often with the Application of Officers for Discharges Since I wrote this Morning, one Lt Blake of Colo. Fellows Regt has Applyed, & it is recommended that he have his request Granted, as he is a Person that will be no Loss to the Army1I am, Sir, Your very Humb. servt

Jno. Thomas

